eNCA's Silindelo Masikane has more. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - At least 2, 000 people have been displaced after fires tore through several informal settlements in the Western Cape. In the past seven days, emergency services and NGO's have responded to 6 fires. READ: One dead as fire destroys 200 shacks in Khayelitsha The latest is in Khayelitsha where 65 structures were destroyed. The City of Cape Town says majority of the fires have been caused by negligence and is now on a drive to educate communities eNCA's Silindelo Masikane filed this report.